This paper involves deep learning for perception tasks, specifically in the area of Vision and Language Navigation (VLN) which involves navigating to a goal purely from language instructions and visual information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the application of the proposed approach to robotics, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper also involves visual information, suggesting that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach that significantly outperforms current state-of-the-art methods, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
